      "id": 12,
      "options": {
        "content": "## 🎵 Music Streaming Platform - Monitoring Dashboard\n\n### Current Metrics Available:\n- ✅ Service Health Status\n- ✅ Service Uptime Tracking\n- ✅ Prometheus Scrape Metrics\n\n### 🔧 Next Steps for Complete Monitoring:\n\nTo get full visibility, you need to instrument your services with:\n\n1. **HTTP/gRPC Metrics** (using Prometheus client libraries)\n2. **Business Metrics** (tracks uploaded, playlists created, etc.)\n3. **Database Metrics** (connection pool, query duration)\n4. **Cache Metrics** (Redis hit/miss rates)\n5. **Message Queue Metrics** (NATS publish/subscribe counts)\n\n### 📊 Example instrumentation for Go services:\n```go\nimport \"github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus\"\n\nvar (\n    httpRequests = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n        prometheus.CounterOpts{\n            Name: \"http_requests_total\",\n            Help: \"Total HTTP requests\",\n        },\n        []string{\"method\", \"endpoint\", \"status\"},\n    )\n    \n    requestDuration = prometheus.NewHistogramVec(\n        prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n            Name: \"http_request_duration_seconds\",\n            Help: \"HTTP request duration\",\n        },\n        []string{\"method\", \"endpoint\"},\n    )\n)\n```\n\n### 🚀 Add this to your API Gateway to start seeing metrics!",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Dashboard Info & Next Steps",
      "type": "text"
